abstract: Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) has emerged as a powerful technique for enhancing the capabilities of Large Language Models (LLMs) by providing relevant context to the prompts that are passed to them.
This talk will show how an advanced framework such as LangChain helps to build RAG application efficiently.
